cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a family of deep nets for human pose regression, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on parameter sharing and symmetry, which are common topics in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions LSTM/GRU cells, which are commonly used in natural language processing, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a task related to robotics (skeleton based activity recognition), suggesting that cs.RO (Robotics) may also be a relevant sub-category.
